39 general with the advice and consent of the senate and subject to
40 confirmation by the senate as provided in K.S.A. 75-4315b, and
41 amendments thereto. Except as provided in K.S.A. 46-2601, and
42 amendments thereto, no person appointed to the position of inspector
43 general shall exercise any power, duty or function of the inspector general

